manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.

manifest.name: MinRanker

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.

manifest.name: MinRanker

manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``

manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MFCCTimbreEncoder
manifest.description: encodes an audio signal from a `Batch x Signal Length` ndarray into a `Batch x Concatenated Features` ndarray.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: ChromaPitchEncoder
manifest.description: encodes an audio signal from a `Batch x Signal Length` ndarray into a `Batch x Concatenated Features` ndarray.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: Wav2VecSpeechEncoder
manifest.description: uses a pre-trained model to encode an audio signal from a `Batch x Signal Length` ndarray into a `Batch x Concatenated Features` ndarray
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MaxRanker

manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BiMatchRanker
manifest.description: counts the best chunk-hit from both query and doc perspective.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: LevenshteinRanker
manifest.description: Computes the Levenshtein distance between a query and its matches.
manifest.author: maximilian.werk@jina.ai

manifest.name: MaxRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MaxRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is the maximal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.

manifest.name: MinRanker
manifest.description: :class:`MinRanker` calculates the score of the matched doc form the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is `1 / (1 + s)`, where `s` is the minimal score from all the matched chunks belonging to this doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: TfIdfRanker
manifest.description: `TfIdfRanker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: SimpleAggregateRanker
manifest.description: :class:`SimpleAggregateRanker` aggregates the score of the matched doc from the matched chunks. For each matched doc, the score is aggregated from all the matched chunks belonging to that doc.
manifest.author: Jina AI Dev-Team (dev-team@jina.ai)

manifest.name: BM25Ranker
manifest.description: `BM25Ranker` calculates the weighted score from the matched chunks. The weights of each chunk is based onthe tf-idf algorithm. Each query chunk is considered as a ``term``, and the frequency of the query chunk in aspecific matched document is considered as the naive ``term-frequency``. All the matched results as a whole isconsidered as the corpus, and therefore the frequency of the query chunk in all the matched docs is consideredas the naive ``document-frequency``. Please refer to the functions for the details of calculating ``tf`` and``idf``
